38struct zt_load_params {
39 dns_zt_zoneloaded_t dl;
40 bool newonly;
41};
42
43struct dns_zt {
44 /* Unlocked. */
45 unsigned int magic;
46 isc_mem_t *mctx;
47 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass;
48 isc_rwlock_t rwlock;
49 dns_zt_allloaded_t loaddone;
50 void * loaddone_arg;
51 struct zt_load_params *loadparams;
52 /* Locked by lock. */
53 bool flush;
54 uint32_t references;
55 unsigned int loads_pending;
56 dns_rbt_t *table;
57};
58
59#define ZTMAGIC ISC_MAGIC('Z', 'T', 'b', 'l')
60#define VALID_ZT(zt) ISC_MAGIC_VALID(zt, ZTMAGIC)
61

78isc_result_t
79dns_zt_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_rdataclass_t rdclass, dns_zt_t **ztp) {
80 dns_zt_t *zt;
81 isc_result_t result;
82
83 REQUIRE(ztp != NULL && *ztp == NULL);
84
85 zt = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*zt));
86 if (zt == NULL)
87 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
88
89 zt->table = NULL;
90 result = dns_rbt_create(mctx, auto_detach, zt, &zt->table);
91 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
92 goto cleanup_zt;
93
94 result = isc_rwlock_init(&zt->rwlock, 0, 0);
95 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
96 goto cleanup_rbt;
97
98 zt->mctx = NULL;
99 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &zt->mctx);
100 zt->references = 1;
101 zt->flush = false;
102 zt->rdclass = rdclass;
103 zt->magic = ZTMAGIC;
104 zt->loaddone = NULL;
105 zt->loaddone_arg = NULL;
106 zt->loadparams = NULL;
107 zt->loads_pending = 0;
108 *ztp = zt;
109
110 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
111
112 cleanup_rbt:
113 dns_rbt_destroy(&zt->table);
114
115 cleanup_zt:
116 isc_mem_put(mctx, zt, sizeof(*zt));
117
118 return (result);
119}

121isc_result_t
122dns_zt_mount(dns_zt_t *zt, dns_zone_t *zone) {
123 isc_result_t result;
124 dns_zone_t *dummy = NULL;
125 dns_name_t *name;
126
127 REQUIRE(VALID_ZT(zt));
128
129 name = dns_zone_getorigin(zone);
130
131 RWLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
132
133 result = dns_rbt_addname(zt->table, name, zone);
134 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
135 dns_zone_attach(zone, &dummy);
136
137 RWUNLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
138
139 return (result);
140}
141
142isc_result_t
143dns_zt_unmount(dns_zt_t *zt, dns_zone_t *zone) {
144 isc_result_t result;
145 dns_name_t *name;
146
147 REQUIRE(VALID_ZT(zt));
148
149 name = dns_zone_getorigin(zone);
150
151 RWLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
152
153 result = dns_rbt_deletename(zt->table, name, false);
154
155 RWUNLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
156
157 return (result);
158}

160isc_result_t
161dns_zt_find(dns_zt_t *zt, const dns_name_t *name, unsigned int options,
162 dns_name_t *foundname, dns_zone_t **zonep)
163{
164 isc_result_t result;
165 dns_zone_t *dummy = NULL;
166 unsigned int rbtoptions = 0;
167
168 REQUIRE(VALID_ZT(zt));
169
170 if ((options & DNS_ZTFIND_NOEXACT) != 0)
171 rbtoptions |= DNS_RBTFIND_NOEXACT;
172
173 RWLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
174
175 result = dns_rbt_findname(zt->table, name, rbtoptions, foundname,
176 (void **) (void*)&dummy);
177 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH) {
178 /*
179 * If DNS_ZTFIND_MIRROR is set and the zone which was
180 * determined to be the deepest match for the supplied name is
181 * a mirror zone which is expired or not yet loaded, treat it
182 * as non-existent. This will trigger a fallback to recursion
183 * instead of returning a SERVFAIL.
184 *
185 * Note that currently only the deepest match in the zone table
186 * is checked. Consider a server configured with two mirror
187 * zones: "bar" and its child, "foo.bar". If zone data is
188 * available for "bar" but not for "foo.bar", a query with
189 * QNAME equal to or below "foo.bar" will cause ISC_R_NOTFOUND
190 * to be returned, not DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH, despite zone data
191 * being available for "bar". This is considered to be an edge
192 * case, handling which more appropriately is possible, but
193 * arguably not worth the added complexity.
194 */
195 if ((options & DNS_ZTFIND_MIRROR) != 0 &&
196 dns_zone_gettype(dummy) == dns_zone_mirror &&
197 !dns_zone_isloaded(dummy))
198 {
199 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
200 } else {
201 dns_zone_attach(dummy, zonep);
202 }
203 }
204
205 RWUNLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
206
207 return (result);
208}
209
210void
211dns_zt_attach(dns_zt_t *zt, dns_zt_t **ztp) {
212
213 REQUIRE(VALID_ZT(zt));
214 REQUIRE(ztp != NULL && *ztp == NULL);
215
216 RWLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
217
218 INSIST(zt->references > 0);
219 zt->references++;
220 INSIST(zt->references != 0);
221
222 RWUNLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
223
224 *ztp = zt;
225}
226
227static isc_result_t
228flush(dns_zone_t *zone, void *uap) {
229 UNUSED(uap);
230 return (dns_zone_flush(zone));
231}
232
233static void
234zt_destroy(dns_zt_t *zt) {
235 if (zt->flush)
236 (void)dns_zt_apply(zt, false, NULL, flush, NULL);
237 dns_rbt_destroy(&zt->table);
238 isc_rwlock_destroy(&zt->rwlock);
239 zt->magic = 0;
240 isc_mem_putanddetach(&zt->mctx, zt, sizeof(*zt));
241}
242
243static void
244zt_flushanddetach(dns_zt_t **ztp, bool need_flush) {
245 bool destroy = false;
246 dns_zt_t *zt;
247
248 REQUIRE(ztp != NULL && VALID_ZT(*ztp));
249
250 zt = *ztp;
251
252 RWLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
253
254 INSIST(zt->references > 0);
255 zt->references--;
256 if (zt->references == 0)
257 destroy = true;
258 if (need_flush)
259 zt->flush = true;
260
261 RWUNLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
262
263 if (destroy)
264 zt_destroy(zt);
265
266 *ztp = NULL;
267}
268
269void
270dns_zt_flushanddetach(dns_zt_t **ztp) {
271 zt_flushanddetach(ztp, true);
272}
273
274void
275dns_zt_detach(dns_zt_t **ztp) {
276 zt_flushanddetach(ztp, false);
277}
278
279isc_result_t
280dns_zt_load(dns_zt_t *zt, bool stop, bool newonly) {
281 isc_result_t result;
282 struct zt_load_params params;
283 REQUIRE(VALID_ZT(zt));
284 params.newonly = newonly;
285 RWLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
286 result = dns_zt_apply(zt, stop, NULL, load, &params);
287 RWUNLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
288 return (result);
289}
290
291static isc_result_t
292load(dns_zone_t *zone, void *paramsv) {
293 isc_result_t result;
294 struct zt_load_params *params = (struct zt_load_params*) paramsv;
295 result = dns_zone_load(zone, params->newonly);
296 if (result == DNS_R_CONTINUE || result == DNS_R_UPTODATE ||
297 result == DNS_R_DYNAMIC) {
298 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
299 }
300 return (result);
301}
302
303isc_result_t
304dns_zt_asyncload(dns_zt_t *zt, bool newonly,
305 dns_zt_allloaded_t alldone, void *arg) {
306 isc_result_t result;
307 int pending;
308
309 REQUIRE(VALID_ZT(zt));
310 zt->loadparams = isc_mem_get(zt->mctx, sizeof(struct zt_load_params));
311 if (zt->loadparams == NULL) {
312 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
313 }
314 zt->loadparams->dl = doneloading;
315 zt->loadparams->newonly = newonly;
316 RWLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
317 INSIST(zt->loads_pending == 0);
318 result = dns_zt_apply(zt, false, NULL, asyncload, zt);
319
320 pending = zt->loads_pending;
321 if (pending != 0) {
322 zt->loaddone = alldone;
323 zt->loaddone_arg = arg;
324 }
325
326 RWUNLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
327
328 if (pending == 0) {
329 isc_mem_put(zt->mctx, zt->loadparams, sizeof(struct zt_load_params));
330 zt->loadparams = NULL;
331 alldone(arg);
332 }
333
334 return (result);
335}
336
337/*
338 * Initiates asynchronous loading of zone 'zone'. 'callback' is a
339 * pointer to a function which will be used to inform the caller when
340 * the zone loading is complete.
341 */
342static isc_result_t
343asyncload(dns_zone_t *zone, void *zt_) {
344 isc_result_t result;
345 struct dns_zt *zt = (dns_zt_t*) zt_;
346 REQUIRE(zone != NULL);
347 INSIST(zt->references > 0);
348 zt->references++;
349 zt->loads_pending++;
350
351 result = dns_zone_asyncload(zone, zt->loadparams->newonly, *zt->loadparams->dl, zt);
352 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
353 zt->references--;
354 zt->loads_pending--;
355 INSIST(zt->references > 0);
356 }
357 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
358}
359
360isc_result_t
361dns_zt_freezezones(dns_zt_t *zt, bool freeze) {
362 isc_result_t result, tresult;
363
364 REQUIRE(VALID_ZT(zt));
365
366 RWLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
367 result = dns_zt_apply(zt, false, &tresult, freezezones, &freeze);
368 RWUNLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
369 if (tresult == ISC_R_NOTFOUND)
370 tresult = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
371 return ((result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) ? tresult : result);
372}
373
374static isc_result_t
375freezezones(dns_zone_t *zone, void *uap) {
376 bool freeze = *(bool *)uap;
377 bool frozen;
378 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
379 char classstr[DNS_RDATACLASS_FORMATSIZE];
380 char zonename[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
381 dns_zone_t *raw = NULL;
382 dns_view_t *view;
383 const char *vname;
384 const char *sep;
385 int level;
386
387 dns_zone_getraw(zone, &raw);
388 if (raw != NULL)
389 zone = raw;
390 if (dns_zone_gettype(zone) != dns_zone_master) {
391 if (raw != NULL)
392 dns_zone_detach(&raw);
393 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
394 }
395 if (!dns_zone_isdynamic(zone, true)) {
396 if (raw != NULL)
397 dns_zone_detach(&raw);
398 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
399 }
400
401 frozen = dns_zone_getupdatedisabled(zone);
402 if (freeze) {
403 if (frozen)
404 result = DNS_R_FROZEN;
405 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
406 result = dns_zone_flush(zone);
407 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
408 dns_zone_setupdatedisabled(zone, freeze);
409 } else {
410 if (frozen) {
411 result = dns_zone_loadandthaw(zone);
412 if (result == DNS_R_CONTINUE ||
413 result == DNS_R_UPTODATE)
414 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
415 }
416 }
417 view = dns_zone_getview(zone);
418 if (strcmp(view->name, "_bind") == 0 ||
419 strcmp(view->name, "_default") == 0)
420 {
421 vname = "";
422 sep = "";
423 } else {
424 vname = view->name;
425 sep = " ";
426 }
427 dns_rdataclass_format(dns_zone_getclass(zone), classstr,
428 sizeof(classstr));
429 dns_name_format(dns_zone_getorigin(zone), zonename, sizeof(zonename));
430 level = (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) ? ISC_LOG_ERROR : ISC_LOG_DEBUG(1);
431 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_GENERAL, DNS_LOGMODULE_ZONE,
432 level, "%s zone '%s/%s'%s%s: %s",
433 freeze ? "freezing" : "thawing",
434 zonename, classstr, sep, vname,
435 isc_result_totext(result));
436 if (raw != NULL)
437 dns_zone_detach(&raw);
438 return (result);
439}

441void
442dns_zt_setviewcommit(dns_zt_t *zt) {
443 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
444 dns_rbtnodechain_t chain;
445 isc_result_t result;
446
447 REQUIRE(VALID_ZT(zt));
448
449 dns_rbtnodechain_init(&chain, zt->mctx);
450
451 result = dns_rbtnodechain_first(&chain, zt->table, NULL, NULL);
452 while (result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN || result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
453 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(&chain, NULL, NULL,
454 &node);
455 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && node->data != NULL) {
456 dns_zone_setviewcommit(node->data);
457 }
458
459 result = dns_rbtnodechain_next(&chain, NULL, NULL);
460 }
461
462 dns_rbtnodechain_invalidate(&chain);
463}

489isc_result_t
490dns_zt_apply(dns_zt_t *zt, bool stop, isc_result_t *sub,
491 isc_result_t (*action)(dns_zone_t *, void *), void *uap)
492{
493 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
494 dns_rbtnodechain_t chain;
495 isc_result_t result, tresult = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
496 dns_zone_t *zone;
497
498 REQUIRE(VALID_ZT(zt));
499 REQUIRE(action != NULL);
500
501 dns_rbtnodechain_init(&chain, zt->mctx);
502 result = dns_rbtnodechain_first(&chain, zt->table, NULL, NULL);
503 if (result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND) {
504 /*
505 * The tree is empty.
506 */
507 tresult = result;
508 result = ISC_R_NOMORE;
509 }
510 while (result == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN || result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
511 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(&chain, NULL, NULL,
512 &node);
513 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
514 zone = node->data;
515 if (zone != NULL)
516 result = (action)(zone, uap);
517 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && stop) {
518 tresult = result;
519 goto cleanup; /* don't break */
520 } else if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS &&
521 tresult == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
522 tresult = result;
523 }
524 result = dns_rbtnodechain_next(&chain, NULL, NULL);
525 }
526 if (result == ISC_R_NOMORE)
527 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
528
529 cleanup:
530 dns_rbtnodechain_invalidate(&chain);
531 if (sub != NULL)
532 *sub = tresult;
533
534 return (result);
535}

537/*
538 * Decrement the loads_pending counter; when counter reaches
539 * zero, call the loaddone callback that was initially set by
540 * dns_zt_asyncload().
541 */
542static isc_result_t
543doneloading(dns_zt_t *zt, dns_zone_t *zone, isc_task_t *task) {
544 bool destroy = false;
545 dns_zt_allloaded_t alldone = NULL;
546 void *arg = NULL;
547
548 UNUSED(zone);
549 UNUSED(task);
550
551 REQUIRE(VALID_ZT(zt));
552
553 RWLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
554 INSIST(zt->loads_pending != 0);
555 INSIST(zt->references != 0);
556 zt->references--;
557 if (zt->references == 0)
558 destroy = true;
559 zt->loads_pending--;
560 if (zt->loads_pending == 0) {
561 alldone = zt->loaddone;
562 arg = zt->loaddone_arg;
563 zt->loaddone = NULL;
564 zt->loaddone_arg = NULL;
565 isc_mem_put(zt->mctx, zt->loadparams, sizeof(struct zt_load_params));
566 zt->loadparams = NULL;
567 }
568 RWUNLOCK(&zt->rwlock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
569
570 if (alldone != NULL)
571 alldone(arg);
572
573 if (destroy)
574 zt_destroy(zt);
575
576 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
577}

583static void
584auto_detach(void *data, void *arg) {
585 dns_zone_t *zone = data;
586
587 UNUSED(arg);
588 dns_zone_detach(&zone);
589}
